				<description><![CDATA[Jo dikhta hain, wohee bikta hain  &#8211; Indian adage and a common marketing technique In India, sales or marketing emphasis has often been on showcasing what you have and the sales automatically peaks. This also is a way to show what you are capable of, as in, taste, quality and availability, etc. This adage and &#8230; <p class="link-more"><a href="https://lastspacefighter.github.io/lapizlazulai/2018/01/17/jo-dikhta-hain-wohee-bikta-hain/" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> "Jo dikhta hain, wohee bikta hain"</span></a></p>]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h6><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><b>Jo dikhta hain, wohee bikta hain</b> </span></h6>
<p style="text-align: right;"><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&#8211; Indian adage and a common marketing technique</span></strong></p>
<p>In India, sales or marketing emphasis has often been on showcasing what you have and the sales automatically peaks. This also is a way to show what you are capable of, as in, taste, quality and availability, etc.</p>
<p>This adage and technique has found its way from a small time shop where we find toffees or cookies displayed to the largest scale demonstration.<br />
<span id="more-771"></span><br />
This technique is now implemented in all sectors be it public or private, <img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-774" src="https://lastspacefighter.github.io/lapizlazulai/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-17-at-11.20.49-PM-300x159.png" alt="" width="300" height="159" srcset="https://lastspacefighter.github.io/lapizlazulai/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-17-at-11.20.49-PM-300x159.png 300w, https://lastspacefighter.github.io/lapizlazulai/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-17-at-11.20.49-PM.png 374w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" />more so in private. I have personally witnessed this as demonstration of capability every time there is a client visit or on-shore partner visit. Every time you have the news of a senior executive visiting the site/location, you would see the entire premises getting a makeover. Carpets cleaned, common areas painted, meetings planned and the site’s achievements are boldly displayed in all possible dashboards.</p>
<h6 style="text-align: center;">Modi Power</h6>
<p>Our PM Modi seems to have taken this idea to a whole new level. He has developed Gujarat as a model site a.k.a. the showcase in the grocery <img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-775" src="https://lastspacefighter.github.io/lapizlazulai/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-17-at-11.21.02-PM-300x196.png" alt="" width="300" height="196" srcset="https://lastspacefighter.github.io/lapizlazulai/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-17-at-11.21.02-PM-300x196.png 300w, https://lastspacefighter.github.io/lapizlazulai/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-17-at-11.21.02-PM.png 384w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" />store. He has made all investment to make the location attractive, pleasant to the eyes, cleanliness to its best. Now that the showcase is ready he makes sure to get all the head of countries like Japan, China, Israel to visit these locations and feel WOWed.</p>
<p>This method is tried and tested. He has proven to be effective in corporate world and small time stores, being a businessman himself. I am sure he would have seen merit in it. While this is an effective way to showcase what we got, benefits in actuals are yet to be realized.</p>
<p>Even in a case this has not been effective, its still finds its way into the global press &#8211; the world knows. To me its still a promotion of what you are ready to offer.</p>
